<div class="line-top"></div><div class="styled-quote">{{StructuredQuote|text=Apartments made with no intent; stairs to nowhere; halls half-blocked; doors lead up; floors cave in; a ceiling hides the sky within. No logic laid these walls in place. No exit signs, just empty space. But in the cracks of tiles and steel, are signs and food; a quiet deal. "Leave what you can," the markings say, "For those who stumble in someday." In nonsense built with little care, it's kindness, not design, that's rare.
|speaker=The author}}</div><div class="line-bottom"></div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Description </div></div>
<center>[[Level 450.1]] is the 10<sup>th</sup> sublevel of [[Level 450]].</center><br>
{{Blurimage|file=Level 450.1 noai.png|caption=A tight corner directing to the sky.|width=200px}}{{Blurimage|file=Level 450.1 2 noai.png|caption=A wide opened window in a narrow junction.|width=200px}}
[[Level 450.1]] is a compact sublevel, characterized by a singular, and expansive architectural structure resembling a five-kilometer-wide, and a thirty-story apartment complex. The interior of this building is populated by a variety of aged, usually destroyed furniture and objects; mostly chairs, tables, beds, and scattered debris, situated unevenly across the floors. The most commonly encountered elements within [[Level 450.1]] are windows, glass panels, and locked glass doors. These fixtures mostly display a strange visual phenomenon: the view beyond the glass presents an open sky filled with cloud clusters, a visible sun, and groups of birds in permanent flight.

The sublevel features unnatural and inconsistent architectural designs. These include ladders, hallways, or staircases that lead unexpectedly toward solid walls or to small, dimly illuminated chambers with no apparent and visible purpose. This irregular construction supports the disorienting and maze-like layout of the sublevel.

Boundaries within the level are a bright, and cloudy sky instead of solid walls. This sky does not appear to have any visible bottom or top, instead expanding endlessly in all directions. Additionally, individuals near the sky report experiencing a sensation of movement, with black silhouettes occasionally seen at the edges of perspective, although no such black figures have ever been documented. In rare cases, furniture has been seen floating still within the sky, appearing to be seemingly supported by invisible surfaces or gravitational phenomena.

Scattered throughout the level are objects, including but not limited to: [[Object 1|Almond Water]], [[Object 30|R.E.D.]], [[Object 26|Moonlanterns]], [[Object 44|Cashew Water]], and additional, less-documented items of interest. Due to the small nature of the sublevel, the available object count is limited, with only 15 known objects staying at any given time. In response to resource scarcity, coordinated works by the [[Backroom Colonists]], the [[M.E.G.]], and the [[Backrooms Red Cross]] have made a system of rotational object placement. These groups intentionally put 2 to 4 new objects during each entry cycle to sustain a minimal supply for wanderers and lost individuals. Informational signs from the [[Backroom Colonists]] are commonly posted within the sublevel, telling individuals to leave objects behind for others.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Entity Presence </div></div>
=== Hills Within a Photo ===
'''Hills Within a Photo''' is a solitary, elusive entity native to [[Level 450.1]]. It manifests as a semi-transparent picture placed within the glass structures placed throughout the sublevel: windows, doors, and panels alike. The entity’s form is monotony and two-dimensional, resembling a person standing motionless on top of a grassy hill beneath the clouded sky that the glass displays. Despite the shape is seen distant and blurred, it consistently presents the shape of a tall, humanoid figure facing directly toward an individual, regardless of their position.

The figure never moves within the frame, but those individuals who make prolonged eye contact with it report an increasing sense of vertigo, with the supernatural sense that the glass is "breathing" or subtly moving. Despite its passivity, '''Hills Within a Photo''' exerts a profound psychological effect on individuals who notice it. Extended contact usually leads to feelings of nostalgia, disassociation, or the compulsion to approach the nearest glass panel.

'''Hills Within a Photo''' shows an unnatural ability to engage in silent, individualized communication with multiple individuals at once. Without speaking aloud, it sends messages: emotional impressions, warnings, or vivid mental imagery, connected to each individual’s thoughts or actions. These communications occur through minute change in the entity’s posture within the glass or subtle alterations in the surrounding reflections. Strangely, each individual perceives the entity responding uniquely to them, usually interpreting its gaze or gestures as direct reactions to their movements, intentions, or even unspoken thoughts.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Human Presence </div></div>
{{Blurimage|file=Level 450.1 prisma 3d.png|caption=A third image depicting the sublevel.}}
Human presence within [[Level 450.1]] is virtually nonexistent, primarily due to the extreme limitations in both resources and navigable space. With only fifteen known objects appearing at any given time and no reliable means of long-term sustenance, the level is ill-suited for habitation. Furthermore, its strange architecture, inconsistent gravity, and psychological hazards, such as the presence of '''Hills Within a Photo''', disable prolonged staying. Most exploration is limited to brief supply recovery missions or scheduled researching cycles done by members of the [[M.E.G.]] or affiliated groups. Therefore, the sublevel is strangely vacant, with the only traces of human activity being outdated information signs, strategically placed supplies, and the footsteps of the individuals passing through.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Entrances & Exits </div></div>
=== Entries ===
* Entering a glitching door in a room covered in sky wallpapers within [[Level 450]], may directs here.
* Answering a telephone call in [[Level 450]], an inhuman voice starts to talk, “The sky now will be the boundary,” and then transports the individual to this sublevel.
* Prolonged wandering into brightly illuminated regions of [[Level 450]], can transition that level to this sublevel slowly.

=== Exits ===
* Jumping into the sky, will lead individuals to [[Level 113]], or back to [[Level 450]] with harmful force.
* No-clipping through a wall with a red shade, leads to [[Level 450]], [[Level 600]], or [[Level 231]].
* Glitching through a floor can send one to [[Level 960]], but its inconsistent.
</div>

